race.comment: CARDIOLOGIST (1) found more like his Victorian best at Ipswich and then gave away a big start there in a 70 and disappointed. Peaks on a 9-day return and a much better effort is likely back to country level. Has the inside gate and gets another chance. SNUGG (10) was quickly back on track beaten 1.4L at Ipswich. Has some weight relief and she will be hitting the line hard. HEAVENLY LOVE (2) has raced okay in stronger races and was expected to go well at Gatton first up, but lost the rider at the start. He has trilled well at Toowoomba since and should be in the money with average luck in the run. DOITLIKEMAXWELL (12) draws wide but resumed in good order for the in-form Webster yard and has scope for improvement.
